title: yes, and?

description.plain:
“yes, and?” is the lead single and ninth track off Ariana Grande’s seventh studio album, eternal sunshine.

On January 1, 2024, an AG7 sign-up link appeared in the bio of Ariana Grande’s second Instagram account, @sweetener. Moreover, all previous posts were removed from the page and were replaced with a pre-save link to promote the single.

The song’s existence was first teased on January 4, 2024, when she was spotted wearing a plain black “yes, and?” sweatshirt. This immediately caught the attention of fans as it is not the first time that she has used clothing to tease a song.

On January 7, 2024, Ariana Grande finally confirmed the song’s title, release date, and cover art via an Instagram post. It was also confirmed by U.S. Radio Updater that the track’s produced by Ariana, Max Martin and ILYA, and the track “heavily interpolates” Madonna’s 1990 single “Vogue.”

embed_content: Read “yes, and?” by Ariana Grande on Genius
recording_location: Jungle Studios (New York, NY), MXM Studios (Stockholm, SE) and Decoy Studios (Suffolk, UK)
